            ]
        },
        {
            "block_label": "text",
            "block_content": "Table 4 presents the performance of different quantization schemes (original, Int4, FP8) on multiple translation tasks, evaluated by XCOMET-XXL and CometKiwi metrics. It shows that FP8 quantization preserves accuracy close to the original model (e.g., ZH ⇔ XX XCOMET-XXL score: 0.8379 for FP8 vs. 0.8361 for the original), whereas Int4 quantization reduces model size but causes noticeable accuracy degradation.",
